Overview

Absurdle is a variation of the popular word game Wordle. Instead of choosing a single secret word at the start of the game, Absurdle dynamically changes the possible target word after each guess to make the game as difficult as possible.

Rather than committing to one word, the program keeps track of all possible valid words and always selects the largest remaining word group that matches the feedback pattern. The game ends only when the user forces the program into a single possible solution.

How the Game Works

The user selects:

A dictionary file

A word length

The program filters the dictionary to only include words of the chosen length.

